 :tx/rationale "Create task: ACP-3: Implement ActionProjection::project() — the core budget-fill algorithm (INV-BUDGET-007, INV-BUDGET-008). BACKGROUND: The project() method is the heart of ACP. It takes a budget (in tokens) and returns a String that: (1) ALWAYS starts with the Action (command + rationale), (2) fills ContextBlocks in precedence order until budget exhausted, (3) appends the evidence pointer. The algorithm: render action -> subtract action tokens from budget -> iterate context blocks by precedence -> for each block, if tokens <= remaining, include it and subtract -> append evidence pointer. KEY INVARIANT: project(b) for any b >= 10 always includes the action. project(b1) for b1 > b2 is a superset of project(b2) content (monotonic fill, INV-BUDGET-008). APPROACH: Implement project(budget: usize) -> String on ActionProjection. Use ApproxTokenCounter for token estimation. Action is rendered as 'command — rationale' on first line. Context blocks separated by newlines. Evidence pointer on last line. Tests: (A) project(10) -> action only. (B) project(50) -> action + top context. (C) project(300) -> action + all context + evidence. (D) PROPTEST: for any b1 > b2, lines(project(b1)) is superset of lines(project(b2)) — monotonic fill. (E) project() never produces [truncated] markers. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/budget.rs"
